article.headline: Florida 80, Troy 58
article.story: GAINESVILLE, Fla. -- Kenny Boynton scored 23 points, Erving Walker found his shooting touch in the second half and Florida beat Troy 80-58 on Friday night in the second round of the Legends Classic. Walker finished with 13 points, all in the second half, after missing 15 consecutive shots. Chandler Parsons (15) and Dan Werner (12) also were in double digits for the Gators (3-0), who improved to 46-2 at home against non-conference opponents since 2004. Richard Delk led the Trojans (2-1) with 15 points. Antywan Jones added eight points and five rebounds. Troy led 32-31 at halftime, thanks mostly to 10 offensive rebounds and another off shooting night for Florida. But the Gators got hot to start the second half, especially Walker.
